        "text": "I have been accused by friends of wearing the 'black hat' too often and, as I reflect on my career, a pattern does emerge. One of being me dissatisfied, frustrated even angry, about some aspect of what I saw as an imposed but misplaced education agenda, or some element of the school I was leading that didn't contribute to learning. This dissatisfaction has motivated me to do something about it, to seek solutions. This anger was not driven by hate, but a powerful belief things should 'be better' and they could be - a [[Virtuous Anger]]. In hindsight these may not have been bold or disruptive innovations, but at the core was to have my school do something better for the students, to have learning come alive. I suspect early on in my career I lacked the courage to challenge the status quo too much. I would certainly not be described as a maverick. However that drive to create, change, improve, has always been motivational for me."
